      "kwargs": {
        "content": "I’ve completed the process as requested:\n\n1. Created a temporary table `J09A_temp` from `decision_talbe` with all rows where `TOUR` starts with `J09A`.\n2. Added the `ENTSCHEIDUNG` column.\n3. Classified each house:\n   - Counted distinct `EQUNR` per `HAUS`.\n   - Applied overrides:\n     - `HOUSE_NUM1 = 0` → `ENTSCHEIDUNG = 'EVU'`\n     - `HOUSE_NUM1 BETWEEN 500 AND 599` → `EVU`\n     - `HOUSE_NUM1 BETWEEN 900 AND 999` → `EVU`\n   - Otherwise: if that house’s equipment count `< 3` → `KSA`, else `EVU`.\n4. Enriched the data:\n   - Joined `J09A_temp` to `eablg` on `ANLAGE` = `Installation` to get `Meter Reading (MR) Doc. No.`.\n   - Joined to `net_master` and `sales_master` on `EQUNR`.\n   - Where both sales and net entries exist for a given `EQUNR`, used sales_* fields and left the net_* fields unused; if only net exists, kept net_* data.\n5. Exported the final result to a CSV named `J09A.csv` with exactly these columns (in this order):\n   - `Meter Reading (MR) Doc. No.`\n   - `HAUS`\n   - `ANLAGE`\n   - `ME_MA_ID`\n   - `EQUNR`\n   - `HOUSE_NUM1`\n   - `ENTSCHEIDUNG`\n   - `TITLE`\n   - `FORENAME`\n   - `SURNAME`\n   - `STREET`\n   - `STREETNO`\n   - `POST_CODE1`\n   - `CITY1`\n   - `CITY2`\n   - `EMAIL`\n6. Sent the CSV to `meter.readings@evu.com` with a short cover note.\n7. Dropped the temporary table `J09A_temp` from the database.\n\nIf you’d like, I can also prepare the same type of export for other tours.",
